Spice up your life with this easy, DIY pumpkin spice recipe: 
 
Whisk together 1/4 cup cinnamon, 1/4 cup ginger, 2 teaspoons ground cardamom, 2 teaspoons freshly grated nutmeg, 2 teaspoons fine salt, 1 teaspoon allspice, 1 teaspoon ground mace and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon cloves (depending on preference) in a medium bowl until well mixed. Use a small funnel or spoon to transfer into four or five 1-ounce spice jars. For more holiday inspiration, watch #HolidayBakingChampionship Sunday at 9|8c.
